ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Date on which survey has been completed
During the past 7 days, on how many days did you eat breakfast?
Notes: 0= 0 days; 1= 1 day; 2= 2 days; 3= 3 days; 4= 4 days; 5= 5 days; 6= 6 days; 7= 7 days

ElementDescription: On how many of the last 7 days, did you have a mid-morning snack?
On how many of the last 7 days, did you have lunch?
On how many of the last 7 days, did you have a mid-afternoon snack?
On how many of the last 7 days, did you have dinner?
On how many of the last 7 days, did you have an evening snack?
Over the past 7 days, on how many occasions did you go for 5 or more waking hours without eating anything?
On what proportion of your meals and snacks in the last 7 days did you eat enough food at each meal and snack to prevent excessive hunger?
Notes: 1 = I did not ever eat enough food at each meal and snack to prevent excessive hunger; 2 = I ate enough food at 1-25% of meals and snacks; 3 = I ate enough food at 26-50% of meals and snacks; 4 = I ate enough food at 51-75% of meals and snacks; 5 = I ate enough food at 76-100% of meals and snacks

ElementDescription: Please report how often you ate regularly (every 3-4 hours) over the past week.
Notes: 1 = I did not eat regularly; 2 = I ate regularly 1-25% of the time; 3 = I ate regularly 26-50% of the time; 4 = I ate regularly 51-75% of the time; 5 = I ate regularly 76-100% of the time

ElementDescription: Please report how often you ate enough food at each meal and snack to prevent excessive hunger over the past week.
Notes: 1 = I did not ever eat enough food at each meal and snack to prevent excessive hunger; 2 = I ate enough food at 1-25% of meals and snacks; 3 = I ate enough food at 26-50% of meals and snacks; 4 = I ate enough food at 51-75% of meals and snacks; 5 = I ate enough food at 76-100% of meals and snacks

ElementDescription: Please report how often you incorporated feared foods and binge trigger foods in regular meals and snacks (i.e., not binge episodes) over the past week.
Notes: 1 = I no longer have any feared foods or binge trigger foods; 2 = I did not incorporate feared foods and binge trigger foods into any regular meals and snacks; 3 = I incorporated feared foods or binge trigger foods on 1 day; 4 = I incorporated feared foods or binge trigger foods on 2-3 days; 5 = I incorporated feared foods or binge trigger foods on 4-5 days; 6 = I incorporated feared foods or binge trigger foods on 6-7 days

ElementDescription: Please report how often you tried to use coping strategies to regulate negative emotions over the past week, whether or not you were successful.
Notes: 1 = I did not experience any negative emotions over the past week; 2 = I did not attempt to use coping strategies to regulate negative emotions; 3 = I tried to use coping strategies 1-25% of the time when experiencing negative emotions; 4 = I tried to use coping strategies 26-50% of the time when experiencing negative emotions; 5 = I tried to use coping strategies 51-75% of the time when experiencing negative emotions; 6 = I tried to use coping strategies 76-100% of the time when experiencing negative emotions

ElementDescription: Please report how often you were able to regulate negative emotions by using coping strategies over the past week.
Notes: 1 = I did not experience any negative emotions over the past week; 2 = I did not successfully regulate negative emotions by using coping strategies; 3 = I successfully used coping strategies 1-25% of the time when experiencing negative emotions; 4 = I successfully used coping strategies 26-50% of the time when experiencing negative emotions; 5 = I successfully used coping strategies 51-75% of the time when experiencing negative emotions; 6 = I successfully used coping strategies 76-100% of the time when experiencing negative emotions

ElementDescription: Please report how often you tried to use urge management strategies to ride out urges to binge, purge, or restrict your eating over the past week, whether or not you were successful.
Notes: 1 = I did not experience any urges over the past week; 2 = I did not attempt to use urge management strategies; 3 = I tried to use urge management strategies 1-25% of the time when experiencing urges; 4 = I tried to use urge management strategies 26-50% of the time when experiencing urges; 5 = I tried to use urge management strategies 51-75% of the time when experiencing urges; 6 = I tried to use urge management strategies 76-100% of the time when experiencing urges

ElementDescription: Please report how often you were able to ride out urges to binge, purge, or restrict your eating by using urge management strategies over the past week.
Notes: 1 = I did not experience any urges over the past week; 2 = I did not successfully ride out urges by using urge management strategies; 3 = I successfully used urge management strategies 1-25% of the time when experiencing urges; 4 = I successfully used urge management strategies 26-50% of the time when experiencing urges; 5 = I successfully used urge management strategies 51-75% of the time when experiencing urges; 6 = I successfully used urge management strategies 76-100% of the time when experiencing urges
